channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Keith Olbermann Diagnosed With Terminal Trump Derangement Syndrome
Trump tells Jesse Watters that he was not warned about gunman, despite reports
item.description: Former President Trump sat down with Jesse Watters to discuss the failed assassination attempt against him. The interview will air on Fox News Channel on Monday night at 8 p.m. ET.

item.title: Trump: RNC Brought $250M to Wisconsin, Hope They Remember in Nov.
item.description: Former President Donald Trump told rallygoers in Michigan on Saturday night that the Republican National Convention in Milwaukee was hosted in a "beautiful arena," saying they did a great job with the convention.

item.title: Sanjay Gupta Has Health 'Questions' After Trump Assassination Attempt; Ronny Jackson Brings the Facts
Schiff's choice to 'abandon' Biden is act of 'selfish desperation' amid campaign fundraising woes, Garvey says
item.description: Steve Garvey says Adam Schiff's decision to call on Biden to withdraw from the 2024 presidential race was an act of â€œselfish desperation" after his Senate campaign had been outraised.

item.title: Trump on Open Border: 'We're Not Going to Take It Anymore!"
item.description: Former President Donald Trump said when he is elected, the country is no longer going to tolerate open borders.

item.title: Steve Garvey Destroys Adam Schiff, Says Turning on Biden Shows 'Selfish Desperation'
Trump says he 'took a bullet for democracy' at massive battleground state rally alongside running mate Vance
item.description: Thousands have gathered in Michigan for a joint rally with former President Trump and his running mate, JD Vance, the first since a failed assassination attempt last week against Trump.

item.title: Trump: 'Laughing Kamala' Crazy 'as a Bed Bug'
item.description: Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump, taking a preemptive jab at his potential presidential campaign opponent, told rallygoers in Michigan that Kamala Harris is "crazy as a bed bug."

item.title: It Just Keeps Getting Worse: Secret Service Reportedly Denied Trump Team's Requests for More Security
WATCH: Thousands descend on Michigan town for first Trump rally since failed assassination attempt
item.description: Former President Trump's rally in Grand Rapids, Michigan, the first since the failed assassination attempt against him, is drawing thousands.

item.title: Trump on Dr. Jackson: 'I Love That Guy;' 'Thank You, Ronny, for Everything'
item.description: Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump hailed his White House doctor, now-Rep. Ronny Jackson, R-Texas, for his care and standing by his side after last Saturday's bullet wound.

item.title: Mayorkas' Infuriating, Virtue-Signaling Statement About the Trump Assassination Attempt
DNC committee moving forward with plans for virtual roll call vote in early August
item.description: President Biden is planning fundraising events and campaign rallies weeks in the future as the Democratic National Convention Rules Committee plans to nominate him via a virtual roll call next month.

item.title: Trump Implores Michigan: 'Get Off Your A** and Vote'
item.description: Former President Donald Trump told rallygoers in Michigan on Saturday night to "get off your a** and vote for Trump."
